<p>The <code>exception</code> tag throws an exception.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}exception 'Exception message'{close}</pre>

<h2>Conditional Exception</h2>
<pre>{open}if $criticalError{close}
  {open}exception 'Critical system failure'{close}
{open}/if{close}</pre>

<h2>Error vs Exception</h2>
<table border="1" cellpadding="5">
  <tr><th>Tag</th><th>Behavior</th></tr>
  <tr><td>{open}error{close}</td><td>Triggers PAD error handling</td></tr>
  <tr><td>{open}exception{close}</td><td>Throws PHP Exception</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Exceptions can be caught by PHP try/catch blocks.</p>
<p><i>Not demonstrated to avoid throwing exceptions.</i></p>
